quarto_titlepages

Templates for title pages and covers

Author
Affiliations

Abstract
quarto_titlepages: GitHub repo with template partials for use with Quarto for adding custom cover pages and title pages to your PDF books or articles. Documentation included for using the provided templates or modifying to create your own.

1 Notes on great-wave

  • classoptions openany (allows chapters to start on even or odd pages) and onepage (same margins on even and odd pages) do not work together. If you set openany, then onepage is ignored. So set openany as class option and then set geometry so that all pages have the same geometry (meaning margins). The code in _coverpage.tex will set its own geometry for the cover page.
  • filenames with _ don’t work across all operating systems. I always forget what symbols are bad in what operating system so I try to have no symbols in included image file names.
  • Use titlepage-geometry: to move your title around so it doesn’t overlap your image.
  • Use titlepage-color to get a background color that matches the image and gets a nice fade.

2.1 Supporting theory

Let \(X_1, X_2, \ldots, X_n\) be a sequence of independent and identically distributed random variables with \(\text{E}[X_i] = \mu\) and \(\text{Var}[X_i] = \sigma^2 < \infty\), and let

\[ S_n = \frac{X_1 + X_2 + \cdots + X_n}{n} = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i}^{n} X_i \tag{1}\]

denote their mean. Then as \(n\) approaches infinity, the random variables \(\sqrt{n}(S_n - \mu)\) converge in distribution to a normal \(\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2)\). Thus concludes the explanation about Equation 1.
